<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="145" pageId="4" pageNumber="144" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1989,2015]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,153,2015]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="145" pageId="4" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,1989,2015]" pageId="4" pageNumber="144">Etymology</emphasis>
. Nanico is a popular Brazilian word. From greek 
<emphasis box="[851,918,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="144">nános</emphasis>
means ‘dwarf’, or Latin 
<emphasis box="[1206,1353,1990,2015]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="144">nanus + -ico</emphasis>
, which refers to the one that has the smaller appearance or the low body stature, like that of a dwarf. The name is a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="145" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,153,2015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,224,251]" pageId="5" pageNumber="145">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Dorsum of rostrum (
<figureCitation box="[561,628,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–10" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1967,1992]" captionTargetBox="[273,1330,306,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[234,1354,273,1942]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–10. Hylotribus nanico sp. nov., holotype female from Brazil, Teresópolis-RJ. 6. Habitus, dorsal; 7. Habitus, lateral; 8. Head and rostrum, frontal; 9. Pronotum; 10. Prothorax, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573508/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="145">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), frons and anterior middle of vertex with dense yellow and decumbent scales. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[356,494,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–10" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1967,1992]" captionTargetBox="[273,1330,306,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[234,1354,273,1942]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–10. Hylotribus nanico sp. nov., holotype female from Brazil, Teresópolis-RJ. 6. Habitus, dorsal; 7. Habitus, lateral; 8. Head and rostrum, frontal; 9. Pronotum; 10. Prothorax, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573508/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="145">Figs 6 and 9</figureCitation>
) with moderately denser yellow scales on median third, forming longitudinal medial stripe reaching lateral tubercles of pronotum and which is larger anteriorly and with a subtriangular black spot. Femora (
<figureCitation box="[253,321,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–10" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1967,1992]" captionTargetBox="[273,1330,306,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[234,1354,273,1942]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–10. Hylotribus nanico sp. nov., holotype female from Brazil, Teresópolis-RJ. 6. Habitus, dorsal; 7. Habitus, lateral; 8. Head and rostrum, frontal; 9. Pronotum; 10. Prothorax, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573508/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="145">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) with dark integumental area at proximal two thirds, and on tibia at middle; femora and tibia with dense yellow scales, tibiae with brownish scales at middle third. Ventral vestiture (
<figureCitation box="[1065,1131,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–10" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1967,1992]" captionTargetBox="[273,1330,306,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[234,1354,273,1942]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–10. Hylotribus nanico sp. nov., holotype female from Brazil, Teresópolis-RJ. 6. Habitus, dorsal; 7. Habitus, lateral; 8. Head and rostrum, frontal; 9. Pronotum; 10. Prothorax, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573508/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="145">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) with each side of ventrites I–IV with subrounded dark spot with dense brownish scales. Elytra (
<figureCitation box="[930,1031,405,432]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–10" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1967,1992]" captionTargetBox="[273,1330,306,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[234,1354,273,1942]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–10. Hylotribus nanico sp. nov., holotype female from Brazil, Teresópolis-RJ. 6. Habitus, dorsal; 7. Habitus, lateral; 8. Head and rostrum, frontal; 9. Pronotum; 10. Prothorax, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573508/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="145">Figs 6–7</figureCitation>
) with humeral callus on interstria 8 and slight swelling on slightly costate interstria 7; basal gibbosities moderately wide and acute at top, subequal in size to ante-apical tubercles of interstria 3; interstria 5 slightly swollen in middle; apical declivity with a moderately developed tubercle on each of interstriae 4 and 6, these moderately acute at apex, and linked by an intumescence that reaches interstria 9 at apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
